    "minides": "The Roma Spider's successor — a front-mid V8 open-top GT with 631 bhp, Z-fold soft-top in 13.5 seconds, and Ferrari's most intuitive cockpit yet.",
    "description": "The Ferrari Amalfi Spider debuted in March 2026 as the open-top counterpart to the Amalfi coupé, replacing the Roma Spider. It is built around a 3.9-litre twin-turbocharged V8 (F154e family) producing 631 bhp at 7,500 rpm and 760 Nm from 3,000–5,750 rpm, driving the rear wheels via an 8-speed F1 dual-clutch transmission. The Z-fold electrically operated fabric roof opens in just 13.5 seconds at speeds up to 60 km/h. The Amalfi Spider weighs 1,556 kg (dry) — 86 kg more than the coupé — yet matches its 3.3-second 0–100 km/h time and 320 km/h top speed. Key tech includes Side Slip Control 6.1, active aerodynamics with a three-position dynamic rear wing, a dual-cockpit interior layout with three digital displays, an 8-inch central touchscreen, Apple CarPlay, Android Auto, SAE Level 2 ADAS, and a wind deflector for open-top comfort. Luggage capacity is 255 litres (roof up) or 172 litres (roof down). Weight distribution is 48:52 front-to-rear."
  },
